  "text": "In a follow-up study, neurotypical participants who performed a picture-word matching task achieved lower accuracy and increased response time with items that were close versus far action neighbors, as defined by magnitude of arm movement and hand action [CITATION_1] . Thus, even though action features were irrelevant to the task, close action neighbors interfered with the processing of the target stimulus. Similar effects have been observed with close semantic neighbors in language and memory domains (e.g., [CITATION_2] .",
